--   constructor.

--   developer, or calling program to your API.
[$sel:apiKey:DatadogConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: DatadogConnectorProfileCredentials -> Text

-- | Application keys, in conjunction with your API key, give you full
--   access to Datadog’s programmatic API. Application keys are associated
--   with the user account that created them. The application key is used
--   to log all requests made to the API.

--   alphanumeric identifier used to authenticate a user, developer, or
--   calling program to your API.
--   
--   <a>$sel:applicationKey:DatadogConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>datadogConnectorProfileCredentials_applicationKey</a> - Application
--   keys, in conjunction with your API key, give you full access to
--   Datadog’s programmatic API. Application keys are associated with the
--   user account that created them. The application key is used to log all
--   requests made to the API.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the destination. For example, this setting would
--   determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newErrorHandlingConfig</a> smart constructor.
data ErrorHandlingConfig
ErrorHandlingConfig' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | Specifies if the flow should fail after the first instance of a
--   failure when attempting to place data in the destination.
[$sel:failOnFirstDestinationError:ErrorHandlingConfig'] :: ErrorHandlingConfig -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies the Amazon S3 bucket prefix.
[$sel:bucketPrefix:ErrorHandlingConfig'] :: ErrorHandlingConfig -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the name of the Amazon S3 bucket.
[$sel:bucketName:ErrorHandlingConfig'] :: ErrorHandlingConfig -> Maybe Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ErrorHandlingConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:failOnFirstDestinationError:ErrorHandlingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>errorHandlingConfig_failOnFirstDestinationError</a> - Specifies if
--   the flow should fail after the first instance of a failure when
--   attempting to place data in the destination.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketPrefix:ErrorHandlingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>errorHandlingConfig_bucketPrefix</a> - Specifies the Amazon S3
--   bucket prefix.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketName:ErrorHandlingConfig'</a>,
--   <a>errorHandlingConfig_bucketName</a> - Specifies the name of the
--   Amazon S3 bucket.
newErrorHandlingConfig :: ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | Specifies if the flow should fail after the first instance of a
--   failure when attempting to place data in the destination.
errorHandlingConfig_failOnFirstDestinationError :: Lens' ErrorHandlingConfig (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies the Amazon S3 bucket prefix.
errorHandlingConfig_bucketPrefix :: Lens' ErrorHandlingConfig (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the name of the Amazon S3 bucket.
errorHandlingConfig_bucketName :: Lens' ErrorHandlingConfig (Maybe Text)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ErrorHandlingConfig.ErrorHandlingConfig

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ExecutionResult

-- | Specifies the end result of the flow run.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newExecutionResult</a> smart constructor.
data ExecutionResult
ExecutionResult' :: Maybe Integer -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe Integer -> Maybe ErrorInfo -> ExecutionResult

-- | The number of records processed in the flow run.
[$sel:recordsProcessed:ExecutionResult'] :: ExecutionResult -> Maybe Integer

-- | The total number of bytes written as a result of the flow run.
[$sel:bytesWritten:ExecutionResult'] :: ExecutionResult -> Maybe Integer

-- | The total number of bytes processed by the flow run.
[$sel:bytesProcessed:ExecutionResult'] :: ExecutionResult -> Maybe Integer

-- | Provides any error message information related to the flow run.
[$sel:errorInfo:ExecutionResult'] :: ExecutionResult -> Maybe ErrorInfo

-- | Create a value of <a>ExecutionResult</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   <a>executionResult_recordsProcessed</a> - The number of records
--   processed in the flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bytesWritten:ExecutionResult'</a>,
--   <a>executionResult_bytesWritten</a> - The total number of bytes
--   written as a result of the flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bytesProcessed:ExecutionResult'</a>,
--   <a>executionResult_bytesProcessed</a> - The total number of bytes
--   processed by the flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorInfo:ExecutionResult'</a>,
--   <a>executionResult_errorInfo</a> - Provides any error message
--   information related to the flow run.
newExecutionResult :: ExecutionResult

-- | The number of records processed in the flow run.
executionResult_recordsProcessed :: Lens' ExecutionResult (Maybe Integer)

-- | The total number of bytes written as a result of the flow run.
executionResult_bytesWritten :: Lens' ExecutionResult (Maybe Integer)

-- | The total number of bytes processed by the flow run.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ExecutionRecord

-- | Specifies information about the past flow run instances for a given
--   flow.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newExecutionRecord</a> smart constructor.
data ExecutionRecord
ExecutionRecord' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe ExecutionStatus -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe ExecutionResult -> ExecutionRecord

-- | Specifies the identifier of the given flow run.
[$sel:executionId:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the time of the most recent update.
[$sel:lastUpdatedAt:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The timestamp that determines the first new or updated record to be
--   transferred in the flow run.
[$sel:dataPullStartTime:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Specifies the flow run status and whether it is in progress, has
--   completed successfully, or has failed.
[$sel:executionStatus:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe ExecutionStatus

-- | Specifies the start time of the flow run.
[$sel:startedAt:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The timestamp that indicates the last new or updated record to be
--   transferred in the flow run.
[$sel:dataPullEndTime:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Describes the result of the given flow run.
[$sel:executionResult:ExecutionRecord'] :: ExecutionRecord -> Maybe ExecutionResult

-- | Create a value of <a>ExecutionRecord</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:executionId:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_executionId</a> - Specifies the identifier of the
--   given flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedAt:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_lastUpdatedAt</a> - Specifies the time of the most
--   recent update.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataPullStartTime:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_dataPullStartTime</a> - The timestamp that
--   determines the first new or updated record to be transferred in the
--   flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:executionStatus:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_executionStatus</a> - Specifies the flow run status
--   and whether it is in progress, has completed successfully, or has
--   failed.
--   
--   <a>$sel:startedAt:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_startedAt</a> - Specifies the start time of the
--   flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataPullEndTime:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_dataPullEndTime</a> - The timestamp that indicates
--   the last new or updated record to be transferred in the flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:executionResult:ExecutionRecord'</a>,
--   <a>executionRecord_executionResult</a> - Describes the result of the
--   given flow run.
newExecutionRecord :: ExecutionRecord

-- | Specifies the identifier of the given flow run.
executionRecord_executionId :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the time of the most recent update.
executionRecord_lastUpdatedAt :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The timestamp that determines the first new or updated record to be
--   transferred in the flow run.
executionRecord_dataPullStartTime :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the flow run status and whether it is in progress, has
--   completed successfully, or has failed.
executionRecord_executionStatus :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe ExecutionStatus)

-- | Specifies the start time of the flow run.
executionRecord_startedAt :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The timestamp that indicates the last new or updated record to be
--   transferred in the flow run.
executionRecord_dataPullEndTime :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Describes the result of the given flow run.
executionRecord_executionResult :: Lens' ExecutionRecord (Maybe ExecutionResult)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ExecutionRecord.ExecutionRecord
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ExecutionRecord.ExecutionRecord

--   Analytics.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newGoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials</a> smart
--   constructor.
data GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials
GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest -> Text -> Sensitive Text -> GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials

-- | The credentials used to access protected Google Analytics resources.
[$sel:accessToken:GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The credentials used to acquire new access tokens. This is required
--   only for OAuth2 access tokens, and is not required for OAuth1 access
--   tokens.
[$sel:refreshToken:GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe Text

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.
[$sel:oAuthRequest:GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest

-- | The identifier for the desired client.
[$sel:clientId:GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials -> Text

-- | The client secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the
--   authorization server.
[$sel:clientSecret:GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: GoogleAnalyticsConnectorProfileCredentials -> Sensitive Text

--   constructor.

-- | The credentials used to access protected Marketo resources.
[$sel:accessToken:MarketoConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: MarketoConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.

--   authorization server.

--   optional fields omitted.

--   fields.

--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   credentials used to access protected Marketo resources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:oAuthRequest:MarketoConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>marketoConnectorProfileCredentials_oAuthRequest</a> - The OAuth
--   requirement needed to request security tokens from the connector
--   endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientId:MarketoConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>marketoConnectorProfileCredentials_clientId</a> - The identifier
--   for the desired client.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientSecret:MarketoConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>marketoConnectorProfileCredentials_clientSecret</a> - The client
--   secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the authorization
--   server.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthCredentials

-- | The OAuth credentials required for OAuth type authentication.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOAuthCredentials</a> smart constructor.
data OAuthCredentials
OAuthCredentials' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest -> Text -> Sensitive Text -> OAuthCredentials

-- | The access token used to access protected SAPOData resources.
[$sel:accessToken:OAuthCredentials'] :: OAuthCredentials -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The refresh token used to refresh expired access token.
[$sel:refreshToken:OAuthCredentials'] :: OAuthCredentials -> Maybe Text

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.
[$sel:oAuthRequest:OAuthCredentials'] :: OAuthCredentials -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest

-- | The identifier for the desired client.
[$sel:clientId:OAuthCredentials'] :: OAuthCredentials -> Text

-- | The client secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the
--   authorization server.
[$sel:clientSecret:OAuthCredentials'] :: OAuthCredentials -> Sensitive Text

-- | Create a value of <a>OAuthCredentials</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:accessToken:OAuthCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthCredentials_accessToken</a> - The access token used to access
--   protected SAPOData resources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:refreshToken:OAuthCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthCredentials_refreshToken</a> - The refresh token used to
--   refresh expired access token.
--   
--   <a>$sel:oAuthRequest:OAuthCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthCredentials_oAuthRequest</a> - The OAuth requirement needed to
--   request security tokens from the connector endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientId:OAuthCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthCredentials_clientId</a> - The identifier for the desired
--   client.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientSecret:OAuthCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthCredentials_clientSecret</a> - The client secret used by the
--   OAuth client to authenticate to the authorization server.
newOAuthCredentials :: Text -> Text -> OAuthCredentials

-- | The access token used to access protected SAPOData resources.
oAuthCredentials_accessToken :: Lens' OAuthCredentials (Maybe Text)

-- | The refresh token used to refresh expired access token.
oAuthCredentials_refreshToken :: Lens' OAuthCredentials (Maybe Text)

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.
oAuthCredentials_oAuthRequest :: Lens' OAuthCredentials (Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest)

-- | The identifier for the desired client.
oAuthCredentials_clientId :: Lens' OAuthCredentials Text

-- | The client secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the
--   authorization server.
oAuthCredentials_clientSecret :: Lens' OAuthCredentials Text

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties

-- | The OAuth properties required for OAuth type authentication.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newOAuthProperties</a> smart constructor.
data OAuthProperties
OAuthProperties' :: Text -> Text -> [Text] -> OAuthProperties

-- | The token url required to fetch access/refresh tokens using
--   authorization code and also to refresh expired access token using
--   refresh token.
[$sel:tokenUrl:OAuthProperties'] :: OAuthProperties -> Text

-- | The authorization code url required to redirect to SAP Login Page to
--   fetch authorization code for OAuth type authentication.
[$sel:authCodeUrl:OAuthProperties'] :: OAuthProperties -> Text

-- | The OAuth scopes required for OAuth type authentication.
[$sel:oAuthScopes:OAuthProperties'] :: OAuthProperties -> [Text]

-- | Create a value of <a>OAuthProperties</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:tokenUrl:OAuthProperties'</a>, <a>oAuthProperties_tokenUrl</a>
--   - The token url required to fetch access/refresh tokens using
--   authorization code and also to refresh expired access token using
--   refresh token.
--   
--   <a>$sel:authCodeUrl:OAuthProperties'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthProperties_authCodeUrl</a> - The authorization code url
--   required to redirect to SAP Login Page to fetch authorization code for
--   OAuth type authentication.
--   
--   <a>$sel:oAuthScopes:OAuthProperties'</a>,
--   <a>oAuthProperties_oAuthScopes</a> - The OAuth scopes required for
--   OAuth type authentication.
newOAuthProperties :: Text -> Text -> OAuthProperties

-- | The token url required to fetch access/refresh tokens using
--   authorization code and also to refresh expired access token using
--   refresh token.
oAuthProperties_tokenUrl :: Lens' OAuthProperties Text

-- | The authorization code url required to redirect to SAP Login Page to
--   fetch authorization code for OAuth type authentication.
oAuthProperties_authCodeUrl :: Lens' OAuthProperties Text

-- | The OAuth scopes required for OAuth type authentication.
oAuthProperties_oAuthScopes :: Lens' OAuthProperties [Text]
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.OAuthProperties.OAuthProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails

-- | Contains details regarding the supported field type and the operators
--   that can be applied for filtering.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFieldTypeDetails</a> smart constructor.
data FieldTypeDetails
FieldTypeDetails' :: Maybe [Text] -> Text -> [Operator] -> FieldTypeDetails

-- | The list of values that a field can contain. For example, a Boolean
--   <tt>fieldType</tt> can have two values: "true" and "false".
[$sel:supportedValues:FieldTypeDetails'] :: FieldTypeDetails -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The type of field, such as string, integer, date, and so on.
[$sel:fieldType:FieldTypeDetails'] :: FieldTypeDetails -> Text

-- | The list of operators supported by a field.
[$sel:filterOperators:FieldTypeDetails'] :: FieldTypeDetails -> [Operator]

-- | Create a value of <a>FieldTypeDetails</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedValues:FieldTypeDetails'</a>,
--   <a>fieldTypeDetails_supportedValues</a> - The list of values that a
--   field can contain. For example, a Boolean <tt>fieldType</tt> can have
--   two values: "true" and "false".
--   
--   <a>$sel:fieldType:FieldTypeDetails'</a>,
--   <a>fieldTypeDetails_fieldType</a> - The type of field, such as string,
--   integer, date, and so on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:filterOperators:FieldTypeDetails'</a>,
--   <a>fieldTypeDetails_filterOperators</a> - The list of operators
--   supported by a field.
newFieldTypeDetails :: Text -> FieldTypeDetails

-- | The list of values that a field can contain. For example, a Boolean
--   <tt>fieldType</tt> can have two values: "true" and "false".
fieldTypeDetails_supportedValues :: Lens' FieldTypeDetails (Maybe [Text])

-- | The type of field, such as string, integer, date, and so on.
fieldTypeDetails_fieldType :: Lens' FieldTypeDetails Text

-- | The list of operators supported by a field.
fieldTypeDetails_filterOperators :: Lens' FieldTypeDetails [Operator]
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FieldTypeDetails.FieldTypeDetails

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.PrefixConfig

-- | Determines the prefix that Amazon AppFlow applies to the destination
--   folder name. You can name your destination folders according to the
--   flow frequency and date.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newPrefixConfig</a> smart constructor.
data PrefixConfig
PrefixConfig' :: Maybe PrefixFormat -> Maybe PrefixType -> PrefixConfig

-- | Determines the level of granularity that's included in the prefix.
[$sel:prefixFormat:PrefixConfig'] :: PrefixConfig -> Maybe PrefixFormat

-- | Determines the format of the prefix, and whether it applies to the
--   file name, file path, or both.
[$sel:prefixType:PrefixConfig'] :: PrefixConfig -> Maybe PrefixType

-- | Create a value of <a>PrefixConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:prefixFormat:PrefixConfig'</a>,
--   <a>prefixConfig_prefixFormat</a> - Determines the level of granularity
--   that's included in the prefix.
--   
--   <a>$sel:prefixType:PrefixConfig'</a>, <a>prefixConfig_prefixType</a> -
--   Determines the format of the prefix, and whether it applies to the
--   file name, file path, or both.
newPrefixConfig :: PrefixConfig

-- | Determines the level of granularity that's included in the prefix.
prefixConfig_prefixFormat :: Lens' PrefixConfig (Maybe PrefixFormat)

-- | Determines the format of the prefix, and whether it applies to the
--   file name, file path, or both.
prefixConfig_prefixType :: Lens' PrefixConfig (Maybe PrefixType)

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials

-- | The connector-specific profile credentials required when using Amazon
--   Redshift.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials</a> smart
--   constructor.
data RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials' :: Text -> Sensitive Text -> RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials

-- | The name of the user.
[$sel:username:RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials -> Text

-- | The password that corresponds to the user name.
[$sel:password:RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials -> Sensitive Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:username:RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileCredentials_username</a> - The name of the
--   user.
--   
--   <a>$sel:password:RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileCredentials_password</a> - The password
--   that corresponds to the user name.
newRedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials :: Text -> Text -> RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials

-- | The name of the user.
redshiftConnectorProfileCredentials_username :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials Text

-- | The password that corresponds to the user name.
redshiftConnectorProfileCredentials_password :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials.RedshiftConnectorProfileCredentials


module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties

-- | The connector-specific profile properties when using Amazon Redshift.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRedshiftConnectorProfileProperties</a> smart
--   constructor.
data RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties
RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties' :: Maybe Text -> Text -> Text -> Text -> RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties

-- | The object key for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow
--   places the files.
[$sel:bucketPrefix:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties -> Maybe Text

-- | The JDBC URL of the Amazon Redshift cluster.
[$sel:databaseUrl:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | A name for the associated Amazon S3 bucket.
[$sel:bucketName:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role.
[$sel:roleArn:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'] :: RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketPrefix:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_bucketPrefix</a> - The object
--   key for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow places the
--   files.
--   
--   <a>$sel:databaseUrl:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_databaseUrl</a> - The JDBC URL
--   of the Amazon Redshift cluster.
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketName:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_bucketName</a> - A name for the
--   associated Amazon S3 bucket.
--   
--   <a>$sel:roleArn:RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_roleArn</a> - The Amazon
--   Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role.
newRedshiftConnectorProfileProperties :: Text -> Text -> Text -> RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties

-- | The object key for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow
--   places the files.
redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_bucketPrefix :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The JDBC URL of the Amazon Redshift cluster.
redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_databaseUrl :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties Text

-- | A name for the associated Amazon S3 bucket.
redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_bucketName :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties Text

-- | The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role.
redshiftConnectorProfileProperties_roleArn :: Lens' RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties.RedshiftConnectorProfileProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties

-- | The properties that are applied when Amazon Redshift is being used as
--   a destination.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newRedshiftDestinationProperties</a> smart constructor.
data RedshiftDestinationProperties
RedshiftDestinationProperties' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig -> Text -> Text -> RedshiftDestinationProperties

-- | The object key for the bucket in which Amazon AppFlow places the
--   destination files.
[$sel:bucketPrefix:RedshiftDestinationProperties'] :: RedshiftDestinationProperties -> Maybe Text

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Amazon Redshift destination. For example, this
--   setting would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion
--   error, or continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of
--   the initial failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the
--   destination connector details.
[$sel:errorHandlingConfig:RedshiftDestinationProperties'] :: RedshiftDestinationProperties -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | The object specified in the Amazon Redshift flow destination.
[$sel:object':RedshiftDestinationProperties'] :: RedshiftDestinationProperties -> Text

-- | The intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Amazon Redshift.
[$sel:intermediateBucketName:RedshiftDestinationProperties'] :: RedshiftDestinationProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>RedshiftDestinationProperties</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketPrefix:RedshiftDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftDestinationProperties_bucketPrefix</a> - The object key for
--   the bucket in which Amazon AppFlow places the destination files.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorHandlingConfig:RedshiftDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig</a> - The
--   settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Amazon Redshift destination. For example, this
--   setting would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion
--   error, or continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of
--   the initial failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the
--   destination connector details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:object':RedshiftDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftDestinationProperties_object</a> - The object specified in
--   the Amazon Redshift flow destination.
--   
--   <a>$sel:intermediateBucketName:RedshiftDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>redshiftDestinationProperties_intermediateBucketName</a> - The
--   intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Amazon Redshift.
newRedshiftDestinationProperties :: Text -> Text -> RedshiftDestinationProperties

-- | The object key for the bucket in which Amazon AppFlow places the
--   destination files.
redshiftDestinationProperties_bucketPrefix :: Lens' RedshiftDestinationProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Amazon Redshift destination. For example, this
--   setting would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion
--   error, or continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of
--   the initial failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the
--   destination connector details.
redshiftDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig :: Lens' RedshiftDestinationProperties (Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig)

-- | The object specified in the Amazon Redshift flow destination.
redshiftDestinationProperties_object :: Lens' RedshiftDestinationProperties Text

-- | The intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Amazon Redshift.
redshiftDestinationProperties_intermediateBucketName :: Lens' RedshiftDestinationProperties Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.RedshiftDestinationProperties.RedshiftDestinationProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.S3OutputFormatConfig

-- | The configuration that determines how Amazon AppFlow should format the
--   flow output data when Amazon S3 is used as the destination.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newS3OutputFormatConfig</a> smart constructor.
data S3OutputFormatConfig
S3OutputFormatConfig' :: Maybe PrefixConfig -> Maybe FileType -> Maybe AggregationConfig -> S3OutputFormatConfig

-- | Determines the prefix that Amazon AppFlow applies to the folder name
--   in the Amazon S3 bucket. You can name folders according to the flow
--   frequency and date.
[$sel:prefixConfig:S3OutputFormatConfig'] :: S3OutputFormatConfig -> Maybe PrefixConfig

-- | Indicates the file type that Amazon AppFlow places in the Amazon S3
--   bucket.
[$sel:fileType:S3OutputFormatConfig'] :: S3OutputFormatConfig -> Maybe FileType
[$sel:aggregationConfig:S3OutputFormatConfig'] :: S3OutputFormatConfig -> Maybe AggregationConfig

-- | Create a value of <a>S3OutputFormatConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--

--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:prefixConfig:S3OutputFormatConfig'</a>,
--   <a>s3OutputFormatConfig_prefixConfig</a> - Determines the prefix that
--   Amazon AppFlow applies to the folder name in the Amazon S3 bucket. You
--   can name folders according to the flow frequency and date.
--   
--   <a>$sel:fileType:S3OutputFormatConfig'</a>,
--   <a>s3OutputFormatConfig_fileType</a> - Indicates the file type that
--   Amazon AppFlow places in the Amazon S3 bucket.
--   
--   <a>$sel:aggregationConfig:S3OutputFormatConfig'</a>,
--   <a>s3OutputFormatConfig_aggregationConfig</a> - Undocumented member.
newS3OutputFormatConfig :: S3OutputFormatConfig

-- | Determines the prefix that Amazon AppFlow applies to the folder name
--   in the Amazon S3 bucket. You can name folders according to the flow
--   frequency and date.

--   bucket.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.S3SourceProperties

-- | The properties that are applied when Amazon S3 is being used as the
--   flow source.
--

--   production environment.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties

-- | Specifies the configuration details of a schedule-triggered flow as
--   defined by the user. Currently, these settings only apply to the
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt> trigger type.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newScheduledTriggerProperties</a> smart constructor.
data ScheduledTriggerProperties
ScheduledTriggerProperties' :: Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Natural -> Maybe DataPullMode -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Text -> ScheduledTriggerProperties

-- | Specifies the scheduled end time for a schedule-triggered flow.
[$sel:scheduleEndTime:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Specifies the optional offset that is added to the time interval for a
--   schedule-triggered flow.
[$sel:scheduleOffset:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe Natural

-- | Specifies whether a scheduled flow has an incremental data transfer or
--   a complete data transfer for each flow run.
[$sel:dataPullMode:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe DataPullMode

-- | Specifies the scheduled start time for a schedule-triggered flow.
[$sel:scheduleStartTime:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Specifies the time zone used when referring to the date and time of a
--   scheduled-triggered flow, such as <tt>America/New_York</tt>.
[$sel:timezone:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the date range for the records to import from the connector
--   in the first flow run.
[$sel:firstExecutionFrom:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Maybe POSIX

-- | The scheduling expression that determines the rate at which the
--   schedule will run, for example <tt>rate(5minutes)</tt>.
[$sel:scheduleExpression:ScheduledTriggerProperties'] :: ScheduledTriggerProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ScheduledTriggerProperties</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:scheduleEndTime:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleEndTime</a> - Specifies the
--   scheduled end time for a schedule-triggered flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:scheduleOffset:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleOffset</a> - Specifies the
--   optional offset that is added to the time interval for a
--   schedule-triggered flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:dataPullMode:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_dataPullMode</a> - Specifies whether a
--   scheduled flow has an incremental data transfer or a complete data
--   transfer for each flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:scheduleStartTime:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleStartTime</a> - Specifies the
--   scheduled start time for a schedule-triggered flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:timezone:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_timezone</a> - Specifies the time zone
--   used when referring to the date and time of a scheduled-triggered
--   flow, such as <tt>America/New_York</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:firstExecutionFrom:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_firstExecutionFrom</a> - Specifies the
--   date range for the records to import from the connector in the first
--   flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:scheduleExpression:ScheduledTriggerProperties'</a>,
--   <a>scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleExpression</a> - The scheduling
--   expression that determines the rate at which the schedule will run,
--   for example <tt>rate(5minutes)</tt>.
newScheduledTriggerProperties :: Text -> ScheduledTriggerProperties

-- | Specifies the scheduled end time for a schedule-triggered flow.
scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleEndTime :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the optional offset that is added to the time interval for a
--   schedule-triggered flow.
scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleOffset :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe Natural)

-- | Specifies whether a scheduled flow has an incremental data transfer or
--   a complete data transfer for each flow run.
scheduledTriggerProperties_dataPullMode :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe DataPullMode)

-- | Specifies the scheduled start time for a schedule-triggered flow.
scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleStartTime :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the time zone used when referring to the date and time of a
--   scheduled-triggered flow, such as <tt>America/New_York</tt>.
scheduledTriggerProperties_timezone :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the date range for the records to import from the connector
--   in the first flow run.
scheduledTriggerProperties_firstExecutionFrom :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | The scheduling expression that determines the rate at which the
--   schedule will run, for example <tt>rate(5minutes)</tt>.
scheduledTriggerProperties_scheduleExpression :: Lens' ScheduledTriggerProperties Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ScheduledTriggerProperties.ScheduledTriggerProperties

-- | The connector-specific profile credentials required when using Slack.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSlackConnectorProfileCredentials</a> smart
--   constructor.
data SlackConnectorProfileCredentials
SlackConnectorProfileCredentials' :: Maybe (Sensitive Text) -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest -> Text -> Sensitive Text -> SlackConnectorProfileCredentials

-- | The credentials used to access protected Slack resources.
[$sel:accessToken:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: SlackConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe (Sensitive Text)

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.
[$sel:oAuthRequest:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: SlackConnectorProfileCredentials -> Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest

-- | The identifier for the client.
[$sel:clientId:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: SlackConnectorProfileCredentials -> Text

-- | The client secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the
--   authorization server.
[$sel:clientSecret:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'] :: SlackConnectorProfileCredentials -> Sensitive Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SlackConnectorProfileCredentials</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--

--   fields.

--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   <a>slackConnectorProfileCredentials_accessToken</a> - The credentials
--   used to access protected Slack resources.
--   
--   <a>$sel:oAuthRequest:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>slackConnectorProfileCredentials_oAuthRequest</a> - The OAuth
--   requirement needed to request security tokens from the connector
--   endpoint.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientId:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>slackConnectorProfileCredentials_clientId</a> - The identifier for
--   the client.
--   
--   <a>$sel:clientSecret:SlackConnectorProfileCredentials'</a>,
--   <a>slackConnectorProfileCredentials_clientSecret</a> - The client
--   secret used by the OAuth client to authenticate to the authorization
--   server.

slackConnectorProfileCredentials_accessToken :: Lens' SlackConnectorProfileCredentials (Maybe Text)

-- | The OAuth requirement needed to request security tokens from the
--   connector endpoint.
slackConnectorProfileCredentials_oAuthRequest :: Lens' SlackConnectorProfileCredentials (Maybe ConnectorOAuthRequest)

-- | The identifier for the client.
slackConnectorProfileCredentials_clientId :: Lens' SlackConnectorProfileCredentials Text

--   authorization server.

--   transfers.

--   Snowflake.

[$sel:region:SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties'] :: SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties -> Maybe Text

-- | The name of the Snowflake warehouse.
[$sel:warehouse:SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties'] :: SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | The name of the Amazon S3 stage that was created while setting up an
--   Amazon S3 stage in the Snowflake account. This is written in the
--   following format: &lt; Database&gt;&lt; Schema&gt;&lt;Stage Name&gt;.
[$sel:stage:SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties'] :: SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | The name of the Amazon S3 bucket associated with Snowflake.
[$sel:bucketName:SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties'] :: SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

--   optional fields omitted.

--   fields.

--   The Snowflake Private Link service name to be used for private data
--   transfers.

--   the account.

--   <a>snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_bucketPrefix</a> - The bucket

snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_privateLinkServiceName :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties (Maybe Text)

snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_accountName :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The bucket path that refers to the Amazon S3 bucket associated with
--   Snowflake.
snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_bucketPrefix :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The Amazon Web Services Region of the Snowflake account.
snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_region :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The name of the Snowflake warehouse.
snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_warehouse :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties Text

-- | The name of the Amazon S3 stage that was created while setting up an
--   Amazon S3 stage in the Snowflake account. This is written in the
--   following format: &lt; Database&gt;&lt; Schema&gt;&lt;Stage Name&gt;.
snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_stage :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties Text

-- | The name of the Amazon S3 bucket associated with Snowflake.
snowflakeConnectorProfileProperties_bucketName :: Lens' SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties.SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties.SnowflakeConnectorProfileProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SnowflakeDestinationProperties

-- | The properties that are applied when Snowflake is being used as a
--   destination.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSnowflakeDestinationProperties</a> smart
--   constructor.
data SnowflakeDestinationProperties
SnowflakeDestinationProperties' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig -> Text -> Text -> SnowflakeDestinationProperties

-- | The object key for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow
--   places the files.
[$sel:bucketPrefix:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'] :: SnowflakeDestinationProperties -> Maybe Text

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Snowflake destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
[$sel:errorHandlingConfig:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'] :: SnowflakeDestinationProperties -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | The object specified in the Snowflake flow destination.
[$sel:object':SnowflakeDestinationProperties'] :: SnowflakeDestinationProperties -> Text

-- | The intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Snowflake.
[$sel:intermediateBucketName:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'] :: SnowflakeDestinationProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SnowflakeDestinationProperties</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:bucketPrefix:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>snowflakeDestinationProperties_bucketPrefix</a> - The object key
--   for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow places the files.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorHandlingConfig:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>snowflakeDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig</a> - The
--   settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Snowflake destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:object':SnowflakeDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>snowflakeDestinationProperties_object</a> - The object specified in
--   the Snowflake flow destination.
--   
--   <a>$sel:intermediateBucketName:SnowflakeDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>snowflakeDestinationProperties_intermediateBucketName</a> - The
--   intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Snowflake.
newSnowflakeDestinationProperties :: Text -> Text -> SnowflakeDestinationProperties

-- | The object key for the destination bucket in which Amazon AppFlow
--   places the files.
snowflakeDestinationProperties_bucketPrefix :: Lens' SnowflakeDestinationProperties (Maybe Text)

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Snowflake destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
snowflakeDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig :: Lens' SnowflakeDestinationProperties (Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig)

-- | The object specified in the Snowflake flow destination.
snowflakeDestinationProperties_object :: Lens' SnowflakeDestinationProperties Text

-- | The intermediate bucket that Amazon AppFlow uses when moving data into
--   Snowflake.
snowflakeDestinationProperties_intermediateBucketName :: Lens' SnowflakeDestinationProperties Text

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig

-- | The trigger settings that determine how and when Amazon AppFlow runs
--   the specified flow.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newTriggerConfig</a> smart constructor.
data TriggerConfig
TriggerConfig' :: Maybe TriggerProperties -> TriggerType -> TriggerConfig

-- | Specifies the configuration details of a schedule-triggered flow as
--   defined by the user. Currently, these settings only apply to the
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt> trigger type.
[$sel:triggerProperties:TriggerConfig'] :: TriggerConfig -> Maybe TriggerProperties

-- | Specifies the type of flow trigger. This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>,
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or <tt>Event</tt>.
[$sel:triggerType:TriggerConfig'] :: TriggerConfig -> TriggerType

-- | Create a value of <a>TriggerConfig</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerProperties:TriggerConfig'</a>,
--   <a>triggerConfig_triggerProperties</a> - Specifies the configuration
--   details of a schedule-triggered flow as defined by the user.
--   Currently, these settings only apply to the <tt>Scheduled</tt> trigger
--   type.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerType:TriggerConfig'</a>,
--   <a>triggerConfig_triggerType</a> - Specifies the type of flow trigger.
--   This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>, <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or <tt>Event</tt>.
newTriggerConfig :: TriggerType -> TriggerConfig

-- | Specifies the configuration details of a schedule-triggered flow as
--   defined by the user. Currently, these settings only apply to the
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt> trigger type.
triggerConfig_triggerProperties :: Lens' TriggerConfig (Maybe TriggerProperties)

-- | Specifies the type of flow trigger. This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>,
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or <tt>Event</tt>.
triggerConfig_triggerType :: Lens' TriggerConfig TriggerType
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig
instance Data.Aeson.Types.ToJSON.ToJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.TriggerConfig.TriggerConfig


module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition

-- | The properties of the flow, such as its source, destination, trigger
--   type, and so on.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newFlowDefinition</a> smart constructor.
data FlowDefinition
FlowDefinition' :: Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe POSIX -> Maybe TriggerType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ConnectorType -> Maybe ConnectorType -> Maybe Text -> Maybe ExecutionDetails -> Maybe FlowStatus -> Maybe Text -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text) -> FlowDefinition

-- | Specifies the account user name that most recently updated the flow.
[$sel:lastUpdatedBy:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe Text

-- | The flow's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
[$sel:flowArn:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies when the flow was last updated.
[$sel:lastUpdatedAt:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Specifies when the flow was created.
[$sel:createdAt:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe POSIX

-- | Specifies the type of flow trigger. This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>,
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or <tt>Event</tt>.
[$sel:triggerType:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe TriggerType

-- | The ARN of the user who created the flow.
[$sel:createdBy:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe Text

-- | Specifies the source connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon S3,
--   Amplitude, and so on.
[$sel:sourceConnectorType:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe ConnectorType

-- | Specifies the destination connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon
--   S3, Amplitude, and so on.
[$sel:destinationConnectorType:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe ConnectorType

-- | The specified name of the flow. Spaces are not allowed. Use
--   underscores (_) or hyphens (-) only.
[$sel:flowName:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe Text

-- | Describes the details of the most recent flow run.
[$sel:lastRunExecutionDetails:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe ExecutionDetails

-- | Indicates the current status of the flow.
[$sel:flowStatus:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe FlowStatus

-- | A user-entered description of the flow.
[$sel:description:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe Text

-- | The tags used to organize, track, or control access for your flow.
[$sel:tags:FlowDefinition'] :: FlowDefinition -> Maybe (HashMap Text Text)

-- | Create a value of <a>FlowDefinition</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedBy:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_lastUpdatedBy</a> - Specifies the account user name
--   that most recently updated the flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:flowArn:FlowDefinition'</a>, <a>flowDefinition_flowArn</a> -
--   The flow's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastUpdatedAt:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_lastUpdatedAt</a> - Specifies when the flow was last
--   updated.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdAt:FlowDefinition'</a>, <a>flowDefinition_createdAt</a>
--   - Specifies when the flow was created.
--   
--   <a>$sel:triggerType:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_triggerType</a> - Specifies the type of flow
--   trigger. This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>, <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or
--   <tt>Event</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:createdBy:FlowDefinition'</a>, <a>flowDefinition_createdBy</a>
--   - The ARN of the user who created the flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:sourceConnectorType:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_sourceConnectorType</a> - Specifies the source
--   connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon S3, Amplitude, and so on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:destinationConnectorType:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_destinationConnectorType</a> - Specifies the
--   destination connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon S3, Amplitude,
--   and so on.
--   
--   <a>$sel:flowName:FlowDefinition'</a>, <a>flowDefinition_flowName</a> -
--   The specified name of the flow. Spaces are not allowed. Use
--   underscores (_) or hyphens (-) only.
--   
--   <a>$sel:lastRunExecutionDetails:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_lastRunExecutionDetails</a> - Describes the details
--   of the most recent flow run.
--   
--   <a>$sel:flowStatus:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_flowStatus</a> - Indicates the current status of the
--   flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:FlowDefinition'</a>,
--   <a>flowDefinition_description</a> - A user-entered description of the
--   flow.
--   
--   <a>$sel:tags:FlowDefinition'</a>, <a>flowDefinition_tags</a> - The
--   tags used to organize, track, or control access for your flow.
newFlowDefinition :: FlowDefinition

-- | Specifies the account user name that most recently updated the flow.
flowDefinition_lastUpdatedBy :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe Text)

-- | The flow's Amazon Resource Name (ARN).
flowDefinition_flowArn :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies when the flow was last updated.
flowDefinition_lastUpdatedAt :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies when the flow was created.
flowDefinition_createdAt :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe UTCTime)

-- | Specifies the type of flow trigger. This can be <tt>OnDemand</tt>,
--   <tt>Scheduled</tt>, or <tt>Event</tt>.
flowDefinition_triggerType :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe TriggerType)

-- | The ARN of the user who created the flow.
flowDefinition_createdBy :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe Text)

-- | Specifies the source connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon S3,
--   Amplitude, and so on.
flowDefinition_sourceConnectorType :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe ConnectorType)

-- | Specifies the destination connector type, such as Salesforce, Amazon
--   S3, Amplitude, and so on.
flowDefinition_destinationConnectorType :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe ConnectorType)

-- | The specified name of the flow. Spaces are not allowed. Use
--   underscores (_) or hyphens (-) only.
flowDefinition_flowName :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe Text)

-- | Describes the details of the most recent flow run.
flowDefinition_lastRunExecutionDetails :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe ExecutionDetails)

-- | Indicates the current status of the flow.
flowDefinition_flowStatus :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe FlowStatus)

-- | A user-entered description of the flow.
flowDefinition_description :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe Text)

-- | The tags used to organize, track, or control access for your flow.
flowDefinition_tags :: Lens' FlowDefinition (Maybe (HashMap Text Text))
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance Data.Hashable.Class.Hashable Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition
instance Control.DeepSeq.NFData Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.FlowDefinition.FlowDefinition

-- | The connector-specific profile properties required when using Veeva.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newVeevaConnectorProfileProperties</a> smart
--   constructor.
data VeevaConnectorProfileProperties
VeevaConnectorProfileProperties' :: Text -> VeevaConnectorProfileProperties

-- | The location of the Veeva resource.
[$sel:instanceUrl:VeevaConnectorProfileProperties'] :: VeevaConnectorProfileProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>VeevaConnectorProfileProperties</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:instanceUrl:VeevaConnectorProfileProperties'</a>,

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties

-- | The properties that are applied when Salesforce is being used as a
--   destination.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newSalesforceDestinationProperties</a> smart
--   constructor.
data SalesforceDestinationProperties
SalesforceDestinationProperties' :: Maybe WriteOperationType -> Maybe [Text] -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig -> Text -> SalesforceDestinationProperties

-- | This specifies the type of write operation to be performed in
--   Salesforce. When the value is <tt>UPSERT</tt>, then
--   <tt>idFieldNames</tt> is required.
[$sel:writeOperationType:SalesforceDestinationProperties'] :: SalesforceDestinationProperties -> Maybe WriteOperationType

-- | The name of the field that Amazon AppFlow uses as an ID when
--   performing a write operation such as update or delete.
[$sel:idFieldNames:SalesforceDestinationProperties'] :: SalesforceDestinationProperties -> Maybe [Text]

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Salesforce destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
[$sel:errorHandlingConfig:SalesforceDestinationProperties'] :: SalesforceDestinationProperties -> Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig

-- | The object specified in the Salesforce flow destination.
[$sel:object':SalesforceDestinationProperties'] :: SalesforceDestinationProperties -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>SalesforceDestinationProperties</a> with all
--   optional fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:writeOperationType:SalesforceDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>salesforceDestinationProperties_writeOperationType</a> - This
--   specifies the type of write operation to be performed in Salesforce.
--   When the value is <tt>UPSERT</tt>, then <tt>idFieldNames</tt> is
--   required.
--   
--   <a>$sel:idFieldNames:SalesforceDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>salesforceDestinationProperties_idFieldNames</a> - The name of the
--   field that Amazon AppFlow uses as an ID when performing a write
--   operation such as update or delete.
--   
--   <a>$sel:errorHandlingConfig:SalesforceDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>salesforceDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig</a> - The
--   settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Salesforce destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
--   
--   <a>$sel:object':SalesforceDestinationProperties'</a>,
--   <a>salesforceDestinationProperties_object</a> - The object specified
--   in the Salesforce flow destination.
newSalesforceDestinationProperties :: Text -> SalesforceDestinationProperties

-- | This specifies the type of write operation to be performed in
--   Salesforce. When the value is <tt>UPSERT</tt>, then
--   <tt>idFieldNames</tt> is required.
salesforceDestinationProperties_writeOperationType :: Lens' SalesforceDestinationProperties (Maybe WriteOperationType)

-- | The name of the field that Amazon AppFlow uses as an ID when
--   performing a write operation such as update or delete.
salesforceDestinationProperties_idFieldNames :: Lens' SalesforceDestinationProperties (Maybe [Text])

-- | The settings that determine how Amazon AppFlow handles an error when
--   placing data in the Salesforce destination. For example, this setting
--   would determine if the flow should fail after one insertion error, or
--   continue and attempt to insert every record regardless of the initial
--   failure. <tt>ErrorHandlingConfig</tt> is a part of the destination
--   connector details.
salesforceDestinationProperties_errorHandlingConfig :: Lens' SalesforceDestinationProperties (Maybe ErrorHandlingConfig)

-- | The object specified in the Salesforce flow destination.
salesforceDestinationProperties_object :: Lens' SalesforceDestinationProperties Text
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties.SalesforceDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties.SalesforceDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties.SalesforceDestinationProperties
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties.SalesforceDestinationProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.SalesforceDestinationProperties.SalesforceDestinationProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties

-- | The properties that can be applied to a field when connector is being
--   used as a destination.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newDestinationFieldProperties</a> smart constructor.
data DestinationFieldProperties
DestinationFieldProperties' :: Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe [WriteOperationType] -> Maybe Bool -> Maybe Bool -> DestinationFieldProperties

-- | Specifies whether the field can be updated during an <tt>UPDATE</tt>
--   or <tt>UPSERT</tt> write operation.
[$sel:isUpdatable:DestinationFieldProperties'] :: DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies if the destination field can have a null value.
[$sel:isNullable:DestinationFieldProperties'] :: DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe Bool

-- | A list of supported write operations. For each write operation listed,
--   this field can be used in <tt>idFieldNames</tt> when that write
--   operation is present as a destination option.
[$sel:supportedWriteOperations:DestinationFieldProperties'] :: DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe [WriteOperationType]

-- | Specifies if the flow run can either insert new rows in the
--   destination field if they do not already exist, or update them if they
--   do.
[$sel:isUpsertable:DestinationFieldProperties'] :: DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe Bool

-- | Specifies if the destination field can be created by the current user.
[$sel:isCreatable:DestinationFieldProperties'] :: DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe Bool

-- | Create a value of <a>DestinationFieldProperties</a> with all optional
--   fields omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--   
--   <a>$sel:isUpdatable:DestinationFieldProperties'</a>,
--   <a>destinationFieldProperties_isUpdatable</a> - Specifies whether the
--   field can be updated during an <tt>UPDATE</tt> or <tt>UPSERT</tt>
--   write operation.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isNullable:DestinationFieldProperties'</a>,
--   <a>destinationFieldProperties_isNullable</a> - Specifies if the
--   destination field can have a null value.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedWriteOperations:DestinationFieldProperties'</a>,
--   <a>destinationFieldProperties_supportedWriteOperations</a> - A list of
--   supported write operations. For each write operation listed, this
--   field can be used in <tt>idFieldNames</tt> when that write operation
--   is present as a destination option.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isUpsertable:DestinationFieldProperties'</a>,
--   <a>destinationFieldProperties_isUpsertable</a> - Specifies if the flow
--   run can either insert new rows in the destination field if they do not
--   already exist, or update them if they do.
--   
--   <a>$sel:isCreatable:DestinationFieldProperties'</a>,
--   <a>destinationFieldProperties_isCreatable</a> - Specifies if the
--   destination field can be created by the current user.
newDestinationFieldProperties :: DestinationFieldProperties

-- | Specifies whether the field can be updated during an <tt>UPDATE</tt>
--   or <tt>UPSERT</tt> write operation.
destinationFieldProperties_isUpdatable :: Lens' DestinationFieldProperties (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies if the destination field can have a null value.
destinationFieldProperties_isNullable :: Lens' DestinationFieldProperties (Maybe Bool)

-- | A list of supported write operations. For each write operation listed,
--   this field can be used in <tt>idFieldNames</tt> when that write
--   operation is present as a destination option.
destinationFieldProperties_supportedWriteOperations :: Lens' DestinationFieldProperties (Maybe [WriteOperationType])

-- | Specifies if the flow run can either insert new rows in the
--   destination field if they do not already exist, or update them if they
--   do.
destinationFieldProperties_isUpsertable :: Lens' DestinationFieldProperties (Maybe Bool)

-- | Specifies if the destination field can be created by the current user.
destinationFieldProperties_isCreatable :: Lens' DestinationFieldProperties (Maybe Bool)
instance GHC.Generics.Generic Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties.DestinationFieldProperties
instance GHC.Show.Show Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties.DestinationFieldProperties
instance GHC.Read.Read Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties.DestinationFieldProperties
instance GHC.Classes.Eq Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties.DestinationFieldProperties
instance Data.Aeson.Types.FromJSON.FromJSON Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.DestinationFieldProperties.DestinationFieldProperties

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ConnectorEntityField

-- | Describes the data model of a connector field. For example, for an
--   <i>account</i> entity, the fields would be <i>account name</i>,
--   <i>account ID</i>, and so on.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConnectorEntityField</a> smart constructor.
data ConnectorEntityField
ConnectorEntityField' :: Maybe SourceFieldProperties -> Maybe SupportedFieldTypeDetails -> Maybe DestinationFieldProperties -> Maybe Text -> Maybe Text -> Text -> ConnectorEntityField

-- | The properties that can be applied to a field when the connector is
--   being used as a source.
[$sel:sourceProperties:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Maybe SourceFieldProperties

-- | Contains details regarding the supported <tt>FieldType</tt>, including
--   the corresponding <tt>filterOperators</tt> and
--   <tt>supportedValues</tt>.
[$sel:supportedFieldTypeDetails:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Maybe SupportedFieldTypeDetails

-- | The properties applied to a field when the connector is being used as
--   a destination.
[$sel:destinationProperties:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Maybe DestinationFieldProperties

-- | A description of the connector entity field.
[$sel:description:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Maybe Text

-- | The label applied to a connector entity field.
[$sel:label:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Maybe Text

-- | The unique identifier of the connector field.
[$sel:identifier:ConnectorEntityField'] :: ConnectorEntityField -> Text

-- | Create a value of <a>ConnectorEntityField</a> with all optional fields
--   omitted.
--   
--   Use <a>generic-lens</a> or <a>optics</a> to modify other optional
--   fields.
--   
--   The following record fields are available, with the corresponding
--   lenses provided for backwards compatibility:
--

--   be applied to a field when the connector is being used as a source.
--   
--   <a>$sel:supportedFieldTypeDetails:ConnectorEntityField'</a>,
--   <a>connectorEntityField_supportedFieldTypeDetails</a> - Contains
--   details regarding the supported <tt>FieldType</tt>, including the
--   corresponding <tt>filterOperators</tt> and <tt>supportedValues</tt>.
--   
--   <a>$sel:destinationProperties:ConnectorEntityField'</a>,
--   <a>connectorEntityField_destinationProperties</a> - The properties
--   applied to a field when the connector is being used as a destination.
--   
--   <a>$sel:description:ConnectorEntityField'</a>,
--   <a>connectorEntityField_description</a> - A description of the
--   connector entity field.
--   
--   <a>$sel:label:ConnectorEntityField'</a>,
--   <a>connectorEntityField_label</a> - The label applied to a connector
--   entity field.

--   <tt>supportedValues</tt>.

-- | The properties applied to a field when the connector is being used as
--   a destination.
connectorEntityField_destinationProperties :: Lens' ConnectorEntityField (Maybe DestinationFieldProperties)

-- | A description of the connector entity field.
connectorEntityField_description :: Lens' ConnectorEntityField (Maybe Text)

-- | The label applied to a connector entity field.

module Network.AWS.AppFlow.Types.ConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided source fields.
--   
--   <i>See:</i> <a>newConnectorOperator</a> smart constructor.
data ConnectorOperator
ConnectorOperator' :: Maybe ServiceNowConnectorOperator -> Maybe DynatraceConnectorOperator -> Maybe MarketoConnectorOperator -> Maybe SlackConnectorOperator -> Maybe SingularConnectorOperator -> Maybe InforNexusConnectorOperator -> Maybe AmplitudeConnectorOperator -> Maybe DatadogConnectorOperator -> Maybe GoogleAnalyticsConnectorOperator -> Maybe SAPODataConnectorOperator -> Maybe SalesforceConnectorOperator -> Maybe ZendeskConnectorOperator -> Maybe S3ConnectorOperator -> Maybe TrendmicroConnectorOperator -> Maybe VeevaConnectorOperator -> ConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided ServiceNow source
--   fields.
[$sel:serviceNow:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe ServiceNowConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Dynatrace source fields.
[$sel:dynatrace:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe DynatraceConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Marketo source fields.
[$sel:marketo:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe MarketoConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Slack source fields.
[$sel:slack:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe SlackConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Singular source fields.
[$sel:singular:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe SingularConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Infor Nexus source
--   fields.
[$sel:inforNexus:ConnectorOperator'] :: ConnectorOperator -> Maybe InforNexusConnectorOperator

-- | The operation to be performed on the provided Amplitude source fields.
